            "text": "Titus 2:14",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " and elsewhere. The translation, “of Him which is good,” is perfectly possible, but does not quite so well suit the context. Some writers (Leighton among them) take the verse to mean, or at least to include, that when men see the goodness and loving-kindness of our lives they will not be ",
            "children": []
